This paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category as it proposes an approach for requirements variability analysis in the goal-oriented Requirements Engineering. The paper also utilizes Answer Set Programming, which is a logic-based programming paradigm that falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the paper involves quantitative preference specification, which can be related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on decision-making and system implementation can be associated with the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) category.
